<p>Update on what happened across the GNOME project in the week from July 15 to July 22.</p>
<h1 id="gnome-incubating-apps">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#gnome-incubating-apps" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>GNOME Incubating Apps
</h1>

<h3 id="loupe">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#loupe" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Loupe <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/Incubator/loupe"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>A simple and modern image viewer.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@sophieherold:gnome.org">Sophie (she/her)</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Loupe is now GNOME‚Äôs Core app for viewing images. It&rsquo;s not yet available in GNOME OS due to a <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-build-meta/-/merge_requests/2242">dependency issue</a>. But everyone can help with testing by trying out the <a href="https://nightly.gnome.org">nightly builds</a>.</p>
<p>This week we have landed a new design for indicating that an image is dragged over the window. Thanks to FineFindus for implementing the groundwork for this. Chris üå±Ô∏è has tackled the task to equip Loupe with a set of help pages.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/07/twig-105/6861b4400867a972d0a6971bf403a8e7948b166c.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h1 id="gnome-circle-apps-and-libraries">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#gnome-circle-apps-and-libraries" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>GNOME Circle Apps and Libraries
</h1><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@dimmednerd:matrix.org">Diego Iv√°n</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="https://flathub.org/apps/io.github.diegoivan.pdf_metadata_editor">Paper Clip</a> v3.2 is here! With a bunch of small bug fixes and improvements:</p>
<ul>
<li>Fixed a bug in which the File Dialog would show all files instead of only PDF documents.</li>
<li>The app has improved its cache usage.</li>
<li>Document thumbnails are now scaled down using <code>Gtk.Snapshot.append_scaled_texture</code>, creating nicer-looking images. This can be specially noticed with PDF documents with transparent background.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/07/twig-105/pWnOsbuvZpoxaLYgfOSfqMWv.png" alt="" />
</li>
</ul>
